  "autoGeneratedHeader": true,
  "intro": "JS2IL supports a practical subset of module syntax by lowering top-level `import` / `export` declarations to the existing CommonJS runtime model and aligning literal dynamic `import()` with the same pragmatic namespace/default interop surface. Namespace objects, re-exports, and common cyclic/live-binding cases work via getter-based interop. This enables mixed CJS/ESM-style graphs for common patterns, but JS2IL does not implement full ECMA-262 module records, host hooks, top-level `await` / async-module evaluation, or import attributes.",
